      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUDDEN FLASH (1) comes off an average performance last start when sixth at this track over 318m behind Clarice Keeping (19.20) in a Grade 5. Better than last start and worth following up. JILLY HILL (2) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling well back at this track, but prior to that won easily by 4.5 lengths at this track (18.58) beating Fear Not Tommy in a Maiden on May 23. One of the main contenders. ACTIVE DREAMS (7) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when seventh at Goulburn over 350m behind Baba Voss (20.63) in a Grade 5. Placed at her previous run. Should be about the money. GERTIE GOUT (6) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.",
